---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Stacks Bitcoin Unleashed 2023 — AES" bodyClass="inner-page">

  <div class="container-fluid event-hero">
    <div class="event-hero-inner">
      <div class="event-hero-left">
        <div class="event-location">London, UK</div>
        <div class="event-title">Stacks<br />Bitcoin<br />Unleashed<br />2023</div>
        <div class="event-tagline">
          Produced at Protein Studios in Shoreditch — the perfect warehouse backdrop for 2 stages of content and 500+ attendees.
        </div>
        <div class="event-hero-photo">
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work1.png')"></div>
          <div class="event-hero-photo-item" style="background-image: url('/images/work2.png')"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="event-hero-right">
        <div class="event-detail-card">
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">Venue</div>
            <p>Protein Studios in Shoreditch gave us exactly what the Stacks brand called for — raw industrial bones that we fully transformed with bold production design. The warm orange and gold palette carried from the exterior window wraps all the way through to the stage and NFT gallery, creating a cohesive environment from the street in.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">Production</div>
            <p>Two stages ran simultaneously across the space, with the main stage featuring a full scenic build and LED backdrop. The developer-focused second stage was designed with a lounge feel — leather chairs, intimate lighting — keeping the vibe conversational and community-driven.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="event-detail-block">
            <div class="event-detail-heading">London Gallery</div>
            <p>A dedicated NFT gallery sponsored by Gamma and Xverse gave the Stacks community a physical space to showcase Bitcoin-native art. Prints were mounted on custom wood panels with QR codes — a clean execution that bridged the on-chain and on-site experience.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-gallery">
    <div class="event-gallery-inner">
      <div class="gallery-grid">
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work3.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work5.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder" style="background-image: url('/images/work7.png')"></div>
        <div class="gallery-placeholder gallery-large" style="background-image: url('/images/work9.png')"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid event-back">
    <div class="event-back-inner">
      <a href="/work" class="cr-btn white ex-padding">← Back to All Events</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
